Three men have been killed in a single car crash on a rural road near Falkirk.The male passengers in a Ford Focus, aged 21, 23 and 24, were pronounced dead at the scene of the incident on Moss Road, near Dunmore, at 18.15 on Friday.A 20-year-old woman, who was driving the car, was taken to Forth Valley Hospital for treatment.Police Scotland said emergency services attended and the road was closed for seven hours for accident investigations.
Segt Mike Thomson said: “Our thoughts are with the family and friends of the men who died at this very difficult time.“Our inquiries are ongoing to establish the full circumstances and I am appealing to anyone who witnessed the crash and who has not already spoken to officers to get in touch.“I would also appeal for anyone who was driving in the area and who may have dash-cam footage that could assist to contact us.”
